<br>
 Okay, one more post.<br>
<br>
 &quot;Brillig says: I _don't_ think that old-style AD&amp;D is much the same as PvP in modern MMRPGs.<br>
<br>
 The thesis is not &quot;PvP = AD&amp;D DM&quot;. The thesis is that in both styles of play, you are pitted against a human-controlled conflict. Whether the conflict is in the form of orcs, kobolds, and ogres (AD&amp;D) or other online players (MMRPG), the key is that you are not just up against a computer-controlled AI.  How difficult is it to understand that simple idea? :)&quot;<br>
<br>
 Not too difficult, but a little tricky, since I (and, I suspect, others) don't accept that PvP is the same thing as &quot;human-controlled conflict&quot; (or HCCvHCC, whatever).  Now, if Scirocco had titled the thread &quot;EVERY P&amp;P RPG is based on HCCvHCC&quot; or &quot;EVERY P&amp;P RPG is based on human-controlled conflict&quot; then I'd've still read through the thread, though I likely wouldn't've posted (much) to it.  Thank god he didn't title it that way, though, eh?  An interesting discussion would've been lost to eternity. ;)<br>
<br>
Take care,<br>
