<br>
<br>
&quot;In my view, the GM is the environment.&quot;<br>
<br>
So, what you're saying is that in a P&amp;P RPG, the environment is controlled by human intelligence.  Thus, in essence, PvE = PvP (or HvH, if you prefer to boil it down to the essentials).   That's my point...you cannot escape the PvP element of a true P&amp;P RPG. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://lag999.homestead.com/files/biggrin.gif width=15 height=15 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/8/01 10:24:06 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://lag999.homestead.com/files/rtfm.gif width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EVERY P&amp;P RPG is based on PvP</span><hr size=1> Sylphan2 says:  <b><i>Now on to this idea that "A GM and a player are not that different". I'll refrain from laughing AT you, but from my point of view that's laughable.</b></i><br>
