Programmer-&gt;species = Human<br>
<br>
Human = Human<br>
Human &lt;&gt; Human<br>
<br>
<br>
If you want to argue that MMOGs would be a lot better (and a lot more like tabletop games) if there was a GM controlling every MOB, you'd get some agreement from me.  But jumping to the conclusion that pen and paper games are PvP is entirely unfounded.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://lag999.homestead.com/files/biggrin.gif width=15 height=15 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/9/01 8:19:08 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://lag999.homestead.com/files/rtfm.gif width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EVERY P&amp;P RPG is based on PvP</span><hr size=1> Sylphan2 says:  <b><i>So I guess all humans are equal?</b></i><br>
<br>
<font size=+2>ARRRRRGGGGHHH!</font><br>
<br>
No, that's not what I said.  What I said was that in both situations you are confronting a situation that is dictated by a HUMAN BEING as opposed to a script on the computer.  The similarity between PvP and pen and paper AD&D is that the thing you are up against -- whether it's a player, the omnipotent DM/GM, or what not -- is not a computer.<br>
<br>
Is it the EXACT SAME situation in PvP and AD&D?  NO!  But THAT'S NOT THE POINT.  The point is that IN BOTH SITUATIONS A HUMAN BEING AND NOT A COMPUTER IS CONTROLLING THE SITUATION.<br>
<br>
Let's recap:<br>
<br>
In PvP, a HUMAN BEING is controlling your enemy.<br>
In AD&D, a HUMAN BEING is controlling your enemy.  (Even if it's not the same human being and even though the human being has a slightly different role.)<br>
In Everquest, a COMPUTER SCRIPT is controlling your enemy.<br>
<br>
NOW do you see how the first two are similar, and the third is different?  I hope so, because I know of no clearer way of stating it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/9/01 8:30:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EVERY P&amp;P RPG is based on PvP</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt;So I guess all humans are equal? <br>
