<br>
I agree that P&amp;P is human vs human....however, the flavor is so far removed from MMORPG human vs human that it is causing many to try to qualify your definition a bit more.  <br>
<br>
P&amp;P human vs human is not adversarial.  The GM human is generally cooperating with the players in his own way to help the story flow.  Not to mention, controlling the surrounding environment to help achieve that goal.<br>
<br>
MMORPG human vs human is very adversarial.  The opposing player has no reason whatsoever not to make your experience as horrible as possible, and also has no control over other characters or the environment.<br>
<br>
However, even given the above statement, there are some P&amp;P games that might fit EXACTLY into the PvP style of MMORPG.   I have encountered DMs that consistantly kill parties for no good reason.  For all intents and purposes....a &quot;griefer&quot;. ;)<br>
<br>
